Subject: High Country Bus Fest: Last Minute Stuff.......

Just 4 more days!........some last minute stuff:

I will be leaving tommorow am (tuesday) for Boone and will not be able to 
check emails,  if you need to get in touch for some reason you can leave a 
message for me at the campground office: 1-800-788-2582

main webpage:  http://www.mindspring.com/~contecmidwest/index.html

VW Trends will be there to take some pictures for an upcomming issue, so be 
sure to clean up that bus!

There will be a children's story time on saturday am led by Lynn 
Blankenship, Lynn is looking for other people who may want to help out with 
children's activities; email her: lynnblankenship(-at-)hotmail.com

Tech Class with Steve and Marc: Steve will work with various types of 
distributors and how to do an ignition tune-up; he will cover replacing 
points and condensor; set the dwell and timing. Marc will be working with 
several carburators.  if time allows, valve adjustment will be covered as 
well.

- POT LUCK/Chicken Wing Cook-Off:   Make em' hot, make em' not just make em! 
  Submit your special recipe to the panel of judges.

We will also have a POT LUCK SUPPER:  If your not cooking Wings - Please 
bring any dish or anything that would go well with wings - celery, chips, 
bread, veggies, pasta salad etc. There will be a lot of people so we'll all 
need to pitch in to feed the masses.

- Full Moon Bus Club Breakfast Burritos:  NEED I SAY MORE  :-) :-)  click 
the link to goto the "grocery list" and see what you can bring to help us 
feed to group......"what we have in mind is breakfast in bed for two hundred 
thousand......"
http://www.mindspring.com/~contecmidwest/page7.html

- TYPE 2 /Full Moon Raffle:   We will hold a raffle to raise money for the 
TYPE 2 LIST and The Full Moon Bus Club.  There will be some super 
prizes......to be announced soon.  Special thanks to Rob Henly and WIld 
Billand Wild Bill for helping to run the raffle

